SIMPLE: scrivener
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Scrivener
<hw>Scrive"ner</hw> <pr>(? ⟦or⟧ ?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From older
<ets>scrivein</ets>, OF. <ets>escrivain</ets>, F.
<ets>⟦eacute⟧crivain</ets>, LL. <ets>scribanus</ets>, from L.
<ets>scribere</ets> to write. See <er>Scribe</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>A professional writer; one whose occupation is to draw contracts or
prepare writings.</def> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The writer better <qex>scrivener</qex> than clerk.</q>
<rj><qau>Fuller.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One whose business is to place money at interest; a
broker.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Dryden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A writing master.</def> <mark>[Prov. Eng.]</mark>
<rj><au>Halliwell.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Scrivener's palsy</b></col>. <cd>See <cref>Writer's
cramp</cref>, under <er>Writer</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Scrobicula</ent>⟦br⟧
\'d8
